         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">19/4/71 ¶  ¶ I am sad, dear Dr Hooker, to learn that our great friend Prof Miquel, has now also left us. What an assiduous and ingenious man, full of friendliness and learning. ¶  ¶ Pray send the few ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.04.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-1881, ff. 12-13.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation: 'B. G. Melbourne) received 17/6/71'.</p>
               </note>19/4/71</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sad, dear Dr Hooker, to learn that our great friend Prof Miquel, has now also left us. What an assiduous and ingenious man, full of friendliness and learning.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Miquel died on 23 January 1871.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray send the few fungi to Berkeley. They may still come in time for his essay. I have to describe a second Australian <name key="Phallus">Phallus</name> of the series of those with a reticulated expanding veil.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The only <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Phallus">Phallus</name>
                     </seg> known to have been described by M, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">P. vitellinus</seg>, was described in B70.12.03, p. 122. See M to J. Hooker, 16 June 1871 (in this edition as 70-06-16a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have just ordered from Dulau the continuation of your icones, which series I hope will proceed quite as speedily as that of your father.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">W. Hooker (1836-54). J. Hooker revived the title in 1867.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray let me know how you and Bentham are getting on with the "genera",<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862–83).</p>
               </note> in order to enable me to judge, when my supplemental <name key="Monochlamydeae">Monochlamydeae</name> must be sent for the Flora<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham (1863–78).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation below signature by John Smith (1821-88): 'specimen of fern and letter to [given] to Mr Baker 17/6/71 J.S.'</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The postscript Is written on a separate page and is associated with this letter because of the sequence in which it is bound in the guardbook. This placement is consistent with the publication of the notes on <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name> (see below).</p>
               </note>
               <name key="Pachynema">Pachynema</name> cannot (after my careful reexamination) include <name key="Huttia">Huttia</name>, but the latter must with <name key="Adrastaea">Adrastaea</name> form a section of <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name>. I have described a second <name key="Huttia">Huttia</name> from Arnhems Land.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">APNI (accessed 24 December 2019) does not list a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Huttia">Huttia</name>
                     </seg> described by M. However, M placed <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Huttia">Huttia</name>
                     </seg> as a section of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name>
                     </seg> in B71.07.01, p. 123, within which he described as new <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Hibbertia">Hibbertia</name> goyderi</seg>, collected by Frederick Schultz from Port Darwin.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
